values:
If you have even heard of Yu-Gi-Oh, you much see this.  Dear god, I haven't seen such pure awesomeness on the internet since.. well, since yesterday.  But still, it is god, I swear.  Pure parody brilliance.

Is this me posting?  Oh dear god no!  It cannot be! 

It must be aliens.

Yeah, I'm lame I know.  I really shoulda updated a week ago at least.

This is gonna sound lame also, but here it is.  I'm busy applying to colleges and being addicted to fantasy and... for some reason I've been suing the time late at night that I usually update LJ writing this random story.  It's about some kids in Florida who steal some moeny.  Lame huh?  Maybe you'll see it if I don't get too irritated at it.  Any way, sorry and hope everyone's doing well.

Renout

*meme stolen from Dalin*

"It's time to create THE SOUNDTRACK TO YOUR LIFE ! List a Minium of 10 to a Maxium of 25 songs that express you and everything in your life and included the title of the movie that is based on your life !"

Running with Scissors: The accident of Renny
(That title was mine long before it was a movie)
Not in any particular order,

1. Dude Looks Like a Lady-Aerosmith (Not a literal interpretation, mind you)
2. Every Breath You Take-The Police (Stalking is my second favorite sport)
3. Holding Out for a Hero-Frou Frou version (Aren't we all?)
4. Livin La Vida Loca-Shrek Version (This is so my relations)
5. Come As You Are-Nirvana (Just a damn cool song, I think you can spin this anyway you please)
6. Cherry Lips (Go Baby Go!)-Garbage (I wish this applied)
7. Here Without You- 3 Doors Down (We've all done the tragic missing people thing, but I've had extra practice)
8. Crazy-Gnarls Barkley (BTW I liked this song before anyone else did, so there :p. And I am entirelly a nutcase, in case anyone didn't notice)
9. From Paris To Berlin (Radio Edit)-Infernal (Yes yes yes and yes, this is me.  Listen.)
10. Livin' on Prayer-Bon Jovi (A very inspirational song, I wish I could live like this all the time)
11. Gotta knock a little harder-Yoko Kanno (GO look up the lyrics to this, and find the song.  Goddamn goodness.  So true though.)
12. I've Seen Better Days-Sublime (My better days were when I was seven and had a tree fort)
13. Desperate Guys-The Faint (What can I say?  Yeah, life is desperate, and so am I)
14. Fine Again-Seether (Seems like every time you look around your shoulder, something else has gone to hell.  Be it my health or my work or my life, I let it slip.  Then I curse myself, and have to start over again, but that's another song ;)
15. Crazy Bitch-Buckcherry (I like this song, so fuck you all.  My next girlfirend/boyfriend needs to be a Crazy Bitch)
16. I will survive-Gloria Gaynor (So shoot me this is a f#$&ing classic, and applies to so many goddamn things it's unbelievable.)
17. Once You've Loved Somebody-Dixie Chicks (Yeah, I don't think we need explination for this one)
18. Not Too Much To Ask-Mary Chapin Carpenter (Just, listen to it)
19. Dragostea Din Tei-O-Zone (No actual relation to my life that I know, I just lsiten to this so much it might as well be on my list)
20. Shut Your Mouth-T.A.T.U.  (Compassion?  The world giving Compassion?  One of the best lies that people belive.  I wish I still believed it.)
21. Shut Your Mouth-Garbage (Interesting how two songs of the same name have such a different theme.  Shirley Manson sings about the influence of the media and public on her, but it can be so easily taken as the outside influence on everyone.  God I love you Shirley.)
22. Bad Boyfriend-Garbage (I make a sucky Bad Boyfriend, but it's a damn cool idea.)
23. Bleed like me-Garbage (Yeah, this applies to everyone who hasn't had that picture perfect high school-- everyone with an emotional sensitivity and a self realization that is.)
24. Fix me now-Garbage (Shit, I just realized I've run out of easy songs and am resorting to Garbage.  I seem to always be able to relate Garbage to myself, no matter how much of a stretch it is.  It's probably because I listened to Shirley through all the difficult times in my life, so I connect everything to it.  Meh, I give it a rest, it's late and I can find more music later.


I just saw Man of the Year tonight, which was all-in-all a great movie.  It's about a comedian (played by robin williams) who decides to run for president.  It has a pretty unpredictable plot, and I truly enjoy the twists it has.  Go see it.  Politically refreshing too.
My step dad recommended 300, which looks to be pretty damn awesome.  Do yourself a favor, go watch this preview.  Looks fricken awesome, no?  From what I'm guessing, it's about the battle of thermopoli (thermopole?  thermopolio?) where the small army of Sparta held off a huge army of Persians.  Somewhat based in truth.  (Ha!)  I read a book called The Gates of Fire which was about the same thing, and it wierded me out.  We'll see about the movie.
Also a possible good movie is Driving Lessons, a Euro movie.  It stars Rupert Grint (Think Ron from HP) as a sheltered kid out with a movie star old hag.  Check out the Preview.

Cool, I have stuff about my actual life, and how I'm messing it up, but I nedd to get to sleep.  Peace out everyone.

So I have been bloody slaving over homework lately, I have so much to catch up on.  I don't really mind it all that much, when I work really hard I can control my habits better, get to bed on time, find balance.  I think it's when I'm stressed about homework that I don't take care of myself as much.  Just an idea, but still, this whole "get home and do homework until you go to sleep" practice is not being friendly with me.  I wanna life, jeeze.

Alright, I got nothing.  I'm busy enough that I haven't really had anything intersting happen, 'cept for maybe DnD this weekend.  That got...   intersting.  Bug me later if you're so curious, but suffice it to say that Melinda's boyfriend is...  yeah.
Dammit.

So let's see if I can get 4 Stat assignments, An earth Science project, and a Scene of Hamlet read by tomorrow.  You Doubt ME?!  What fools...  I'll only be up till 5...

So we're baaaaack!  And camping was fun shit.  I mean really fun.  Got to go out into the canyons finally, it's been way too long.  I got to do some Lick-Rock scrambling, up and down and backwards and into AP ruins, (Read: Ancestral-Puebloan, the really dumb political correct name we have to call the anisazi now)found a sick new site with a whole ton of pottery, and generally had a good time.  For those who aren't in the southwest, we just had a HUGE storm, and just about every river is running to max.  In the desert this means that all sorts of new features were uncovered, so the pottery we found has probably now been seen by anyone for a good 800 years.  How fricken cool is that? 

So now I'm back... and not exactly sure what to do now.  I guess I should do some work on my English, and I can probably handle it since it's Hamlet.  Shakespeare is good, Renny can handle it.  THe normal English-let's-anylize-this-for-some-bullshit-that-isn't-actually-there stuff is offset by the fact that I really like Shakespeare.  I mean, how can you not?  It just sounds damn cool.
Anyway, I should probably get on that eventually.  But I hope to get some decent music, cause if I don't I may just keel over and die.  I nnnnneeeeeeddddd a new cd.  NEEEED.  I don't know why, I just need one.

Oh, the big news is that I've teken myself off my medication.  SInce this is what has kept me stable for the past year, this is a big step.  I forsee some intersting things coming up.  Already, I'm getting dizzy spells, and uncontrolable fits of mood.  We'll see if I can handle it.  
No one tell my parents though.  Doing this now with no one observing is what they'd call a bad idea, and probably for good reason.  But if I did actually "smart" things where my health was concerned, then I wouldn't be Renny, wo9uld I?  This may backfire and bite me in the ass, but if I can get off this medicen...

That would be awesome.

So wish me luck everyone, and if you have free time tomorrow (Columbus day) call me up and lets do something.  To hell with all this responsibility if I can't have a hang day every once in a while.

So when I said that whole "I am now asexual thing" it wasn't ment to be all that serious.  After all, it's not like I can control my hormones or anything...


..Or can I?  (Dun dun duuuuuun!)

In the past three weeks I have had not one, but three opportunities for cool dates.  People who through some bizarre act of nature are attracted to me, and would most likely go out with me if I asked them.  I mentioned one before, one is a band mate, and the other is a long time friend.  ANd the really bizarre thing is I have no strong desire to do anything resembling dating right now.  Murphy's Law is apparently working on overtimes lately.
How the hell did this happen?  I have no clue.  It might be all the drugs (light ones, no one freak please) that I've been taking lately, or it might be the fact that with my new found chemical aids, I am so totally comfortable with myself and my appearance for only the first time ever.  Wild how these just sort of.. happen.  I feel vaguely uneasy, just cause with the way the world seems to be working all three will hate me the second I deciede to try to date them.  But besides this minor superstitious nature of mine, I think we're doing kinda well.

I will, however, spontaniously combust if I do not get some more music.  Anyone have awesome CD's that I should buy?  Please give suggestions!!!

Shit, I have to go.  The family is going camping in Canyonlands area for the next two days.  I'll be back monday, maybe I can finish this then.  Peace, and
REni out.

So yea, I've been really busy lately.  I'll admitt, some of that being busy involves playing a lot of Counter-Strike, but I thinks that's justified after a summer of deprivation.

I'm still working on English, so I don't have time for anything but a quick summery.
Anime club is Awesome.  I wasn't quite sure how it was going to turn out, but I am just thrilled to be  part of it, and the stuff we shall do.  Party on.

I need ot get off my ass and dosome college stuff.  I graduate in a few months, and I need to do my senior portfolio, craft a list of colleges to apply to and apply to them.  This somewhat contrasts with my next plan: get really high.  I got a good connection today at school, and with some luck I will have a supply of Marijuana and Empathy before the week is out.  If someone knows how to get high, and stay motivated, I would love you forever.  Otherwise, getting high may have to wait. 
Crazy isn't it?  But my priorities have changed quite a bit in the last few weeks.  I sorta feel actually motivated to get my life going, get off to college, do stuff this year, and make something of myself.  I sure didn't see that coming. 

Of course, the first step in that long line of priorities is to get this english done and get some sleep.  I haven't even had time to take a shower since Tuesday and I am sleep depreived beyond the point I can really deal with.  So I'll catch up with everyone later, love you all.

So I was a total geek today, taking apart every bit of our phone line and DSL system trying to figure out how it worked.  In the end, a piece of ethernet cable, the extra socket on the wireless box, and my brain made beautiful music together.  And now I sit here writing on my LJ for the first time in my room.  Horah!

The irony is I don't really have time to give a good journal entry.  Somehow, I think I have the self-control to get to bed ontime tonight.  Cheer with me firends, for I may pass english just yet.  Or maybe not.

The nice thing about homework, is that with enough of it, and a few good fantasy books, I can ignore the fact that I'm 18, have hormones, and have obsessions.  Yay!

Wow, I have been so happy the past couple of weeks I don't know what to do with myself.  It doesn't seem right.  I mean really, Am'y I supposed to get depressed when people betray my trust/insult me/ act like assholes/ are viscious?  (That is only singling out seven people, no one inparticular)
Yet I'm doing just fine.  This confuses me.

Oh well, it hasn't hurt me yet.  Party anyone?

SO for a long while there, I thought my Garbage days were gone.  Guess not.  I just needed some time to spred out, and there they are, hammering on the spearkers.  It's almost stunning how good I feel.  Whice is bizaare, sense every memory I have of listening to Garbage has either been when I was insanely depressed, or just narcissistically nihilistic.  (Hehe, that's fun to say)  Not that I'm feeling any different now, but this music just gets me feeling great!.  It probably has something to do with the fact that I am on my own for tonight, no parents.  God that feels good.  Funny how I can't get anything done with them in the house, even though they constantly nag me to do shit.  See, now, for some bizarre reason, I have gotten more accomplished than I have in the rest of this week. 
You should be sleeping my love
Tell me what you're dreaming of
Funny how dinner tastes better when I make it for myself, and just for myself.  Homework in easy, barely a burden at all.  I think I'll do just fine in college.
Sweat it all out
Sweat it all out
With your bedroom eyes and your baby pout
Sweat it all out
In our electric storms and our shifting sands
and our candy jars and our sticky hands 

I apologize for my random montage.  

Without pictures.  That's possible, right?  a pictureless montage...

Anyway, life seems to be good, if uncertain, for I remain here in Durango trying to get some college credit next sumester.  We shall see.

So I should check my food.  Lova ya all.

Has anyone seen the new spidy preview?  I'm going to be the first to say it, cause I know I won't hear the end of it till doom's day, Parker is Emo.  Okay, we got it over with.  Now no one should have to even say that again, right?

Fuck.

My favorite spider also appears to be cheating on his love, which I will say is NOT COOL!
Besides the who cheating-thing, which I shouldn't judge cause I haven't seen the damn movie, he FUCKING CHEATED ON A RED HEAD!!!   THIS TYPE OF THING SHOULD BE OUTLAWED BY THE FRICKEN GENEVA CONVENTION OR SOMETHING!!!  YOU DO NOT CHEAT ON A RED HEAD IF YOU HAVE ONE!!!!!  (and I should shut up because I can't remember her name.  still.)

Now that I've gotten my years worth of upper case immature rantning out of the way, 
I need to go to bed.

Reni has been way sick/plastered for the last three days, staying in bed and feeling sorry for himself.  It should end, now.  Preferably with no makeup work needed.  RIght.  I've been so bloody tired I don't know what to do with myself.  Walking around the block reduces me to a pile of shambling biomass, and my block is very short.  My latest cure is oshia (?) root tea, which makes me feel better,  but tastes about like you'd expect a random root duge out of the ground and boiled in water to taste like.  No es bien.

So I'm going to try and get out of the house.  If I pass out in the park, then I pass out in the park.  What will be, will be.  

One last thing.  I was shocked after my last posting, I got 5 emails from random people who thought my world was being put upside-down.  Now first of all, I was pretty damn sure that five people didn't even read my journal, much less care about it.  I was expecting that one ta two people.  Then, that so many people thought it was a change, was also upexpected.  I thought that this wouldn't be too strange considering how I normally act, but I guess I was wrong.  Just to put the inevitable questioning  down, I am not gay.  I have enjoyed girls, and will always continue to enjoy them.  THis simply says I'm complicated, and cannot be sumerized ina simple statement like 'heterosexual".    Juicy, like a lot of life.  I refuse to simplify myself to a single word.  So there :p.

NOW, to raid the library for more Lackey, and try and forget the english essay that was supposed to be due monday.

So.


SO.

Er.  Well.
KENNY is now dead.  you killed Kenny, you bastards.  
Hehe...  
This may be the first journal in a while that isn't full of angst.  Partially full, but not entirely.  I hope no one is upset by this.

So for the first time since earlier this summer, maybe, say, july, I feel that I have my life under control.  I feel confident about my school work, I feel confident about my school future, I feel confident about my family and home.  For the first time in years, I am on a consistantly good basis with my brother, which makes me incredibly happy.  Somehow, and for some reason, god deceided I could be in control of every part of my life for a while.  More than ever before, I feel stable, like I have somewhere to stand if it all goes to hell.  Partly I don't know how to handle this, but mostly I'm just savouring the bliss.  Sweet, tasty control.  Over everything.

Well, except love of course.   That one is just the fuck out of my control.  Without Dalin around, and with the knowledge that I am going to see her exactly one week in the all of the next year, my life sorta fell of a cliff.  My hormones responded by taking up a lost cause from years ago.  Stupid, but not under my control.  Now the same target is irreversably out of range.  Great.  This has happened before.  Now get over it.  

Why can't I just listen to myself?
Being love sick is not entirely the problem, since after being in the said state for approxmately 4 years straight of my life, I'm used to it.  Yeah, heart breaks, cry in bed every night, bad dreams, emotionaly unstable, bad moods, blah blah.  Get on with it.  Eat Ice Cream, get wasted and stoned, experiment with dangerous substances, take risks, and I can deal.  Maybe even come out a little more alive at the end.  But what is bothering me is this is delaying a new relationship.  

I should confess something.  Or not really confess, but own up to what most of you probably know already.  Renny is so not fucking straight.  Not even bent.  Sometime this year I looked at myself in the mirror, and admitted that I'm as curved as the bleeding coastline of Hawaii.  Great.  No biggy, after all my random experimentation with my hormones, this is to be expected that I don't stick with anything.  Call it a phase, call me bisexual, I don't bloody care, but I will like guys and there's nothing I can do about it.  
And...  my second potential date just showed up the other day.  One that won't move to the bristish Virgin Islands.  What can I say...  he's cute, shy, most likely bi or gay, so nice and wonderful, and seems to like me.  However I see him asking me out perhaps by the time hell freezes.  The ball is in my court, and I need to do some getting-over-shit very soon.  I got trashed in a relationship again.  Great.  It was partly my fault, but even in my most self-blaming mood, I cannot even try to take full responsibility for the breakup.  Actually, that isn't my fault at all.  Which of course doesn't make it any easier.  
So here I am, with everything else figured out, and hitting my head against a metaphorical wall of stupid emotional attachment.  Whos fault is this, now, that I can't let go?

I plead the fifth amendment.


Grr, on to things I'm actually succeeding at.
The first foundation band performance is tomorrow and I'm excited.  It's almost the same band I toured with the whole summer, the Excel Steel Pan Ansamble, but with a few different people.  Unlike this summer, I've been working very hard to practice and play for this band.  I'm used to thinking of band as a social thing-- I play, and in return I get to hang out with awesome people, cute chicks and cute guys.  (The new guitarist, oooooo).  Lately, though, I've been really enjoying just playing them music.  I may be dancing around and looking foolish and like I'm just trying to attract attention, but more than ever I just love playing in the damn band.  I got a few new parts on piano that I've just fallen in love with, and I love to hear the others play.  We rock!!!  Everyone wish us luck tomorrow at the Coffee festival, should be a blast.  Yeah!

I just got my own blockbuster card the other day.  I've been renting a couple a movies for the last few days, and just watching stuff that I want to watch.  So far I've already added two absolute favorites to my list, Underworld Evolution and Borne Identity.  I didn't think either one would even be decent, much less incredible.  Yet I stand corrected.  I love movies that have a strong main theme, but in which a love theme runs parallel to.    Not the main focus, but as a sort of goal for the protagonists.  These type of themes really leave me feeling fulfilled, like that's what I want in life.  Someone to share everything with, and stay with forever.  Granted, I might not find that until I can calm myself down a bit, but it gives me a hope, a glimps of something to strive for.  Hero (Jet Lee) was also another unexpectedly decent movie.  Not stunning, but entirely unpredictable, which is a wonderful change for those big budget Chinese movies.  Besides those, I have nothing else to crow about.

I've also got back into my fantasy reading.  I'm going through all Mercedes Lackey's books again, and re-reading everything I can find.  It's a cool experience for me, since I read most of these books when I was 10 and 12, so I notice all osrts of new things.  I wrote a letter to here in late July, and two days ago, I actually got a reply!  Lackey answered a plot question I had to my complete satisfaction, and earned herself a fan for life.  No more library for me, I'm buying here books straight from her website now.

What else, hmmm.  I'm making a bunch of friends at school lately.  DHS has a lot of bastards, morons and bitches, but it has it's share of cool people two.  I took Jesslyn, a girl from englsih tubing last weekend and loved it.  We froze to death, but it was totally worth it in my mind.  Jess is just one of those amazing people who you stumble on and get  along with better than people you've known your entire life.  Oh, i have a funny story about that!  Someone...  I forget who, but someone asked me if I was dating her.  Me!  Okay, maybe only I find that funny, but you would is you knew Jess.  How could she be anthing but your best friend?  I just can't comprehend it.  But I digress.
I've also managed to make a few pearls in friendship, as the saying goes.  People who you wouldn't normally think of, the shy girl in the corner, the boy who shares at things but never say anything.  That pretty accuratly describes Mia and Brent, two very cool people who I have had the pleasure of befriending.  Also Ethan, the juggler who is missing a few pieces in the head.  This of couse, makes him all the more intersting.  I also hang with Jenelle, the cool chick who used to go to Excel.  I don't see Ale very much, but i have lunch with her whenever I can and god I love her!  She's just about the sweetest, most wonderful person I've ever known.  Second only, possibly to Glen.  But jeeze, I'm just ranting.  People are cool!  I wish I had five clones so I could spend a lifetime just socializing.

Socializing, along with some other things, is taking time from exercise.  I get a good half an hour of hard biking in every day, but not much else.  I'm looking for something fun, but very active to do this winter, I don't think Skiing will be enough.  Anyone got some ideas?

So that's a slice of my life right now, I have tons more but I needs to go to bed, and I'll be amazed if anyone gets their way through all of this as it is.  Just know, I love you all, and wish you the best of lives.  May you always find water and shade.

SO I sit here with a stolen lapton in my room, repeating certain songs on my ipod, and desperetly trying to get myself to write an essay.  On existentialism.

Yeah, yeah, I know; the irony is indeed killing me.  However irony doesn't seem to be helping me write this damn thing, so no luck there.  In fact, as time grows, it just seems to be more and more difficult.

Blerg, I am hating english.  I used to be so good at it, now evry essay I write seems like I'm stabbing my own eyes out, slowly.
With a fork.

What is probably the reason is simple dread.  I have a bad habit of putting off difficult and uncomfortable things, often until they either dissapear or blow up in my face.  This is neither smart nor responsible; one day I am just going to have to face myself.  Sometimes it works out alright; I can get the easy stuff done first, then use my remaining time to finish the difficulties.

What end up happening, though, is I procrastinate until it's too fricken late, and screw myself over.  Thus with this essay.  I knew I had to do it when I got home this afternoon, but I decieded to watch Cowboy Bebop all night instead.  It's now 10:00, and I still have no idea what I'm going to write for a complicated and difficult essay.  Bloody hell, someone help me.  God, this would be an ideal time to bail out your foolish child here.  What about it?

Blerg.  

The sad thing is I almost want to go back to my depression/love sickness of yesterday, if only it ment this essay could be out of my life.  THe problem seems to be that the more I agonisze over it, the more difficult it becomes.  And I've spent no lack of time agonizing over it.  At least romaticism can be solved by something.  (That would be hitting my head against the wall until I forget about it.  Novel, doncha think?)  This essay, however, will still be here when my skull cracks.

Jesus Christ, help me!!

Grrr, I need to stop being so depressed.  It isn't that I don't have my reasons, -- I always do, but there is no decent reason why I should ever be depressed again.  Ever.  It's never helped anything.  Love, Life, School and Work can just go suck it, cause I'm sick of being sad through band and school, after school and during the weekends, goddammit.  Not that I'm depressed through those times, it just seems like I have a required minimum of 5 horrible minutes per half hour.  
Complain, bitch rant, bitch, argue, criticize, whine.  I suck and I know it.  Now to fix this whole situation...

I need more sleep.

And I need an angel.  Anyone got a backup handy?

So, despite my apparent motives, I'm not giving up this journal.  Lately, things have gone in the "Private" category, and despite evidence to the obvious, I do realize the need to privatize stuff.  Most likely I will be coming back to this journal once my personal life stops gliching so much, and the rest of my work calms down.  Read: When I finish my summer reading.  (School started wenesday of last week.)

So I finally got back to DnD, and twas awesomeness.  Killashandra, my character, however, suffered an unfortunet backstab by Suzanne's character.  The situation was something like this; we were in a harrowed situation, and Killy had the bright notion of starting the battle.  She probably could have won it given two more rounds, but Suzanne and Alex's characters decided that the only way to survive was to burtally betray me to gain the favour of our enemies.  (I'm not convinced of the legitamacy of this, but that's what you get when you party with a Vampire.  Phillipe's character suffered the same fate, and was very upset.  I was upset too, but recent lessons in loss managed to prevent me from getting bitter at my friends, unlike Phi.  I'm still really sad though.  Killy is not fully gone, thankgod, but she's out of action for a considerable time.  while she gets brought back to life, I'm planning on playing a backup character (who happens to be her brother) that I've been wanting to play for quite some time now.   I won't chance spilling his secrets quite yet, but he is going to be a blast, simply because no one will know what to expect from him.  Killashandra, while fun to play, has very simple motivations.  So I anxiously look forwards to next weekend.

Grrr, I've been searching for the alternate sheet music to pachobell's Canon for wuite some time now, and have yet to find it.  Alex, in her awesomeness tried to scan and copy it for me, but copied the wrong part.  Ale has been in the interesting mood of first staying away and ignoring me, then being friendly.  While this is human behaviour and everyone does it, it still confuses the hell out of me.  But I will still give her my soul for this music.

Letssee, school's alright, but I really want to get done with high school.  In a few months, if possible.  Then I'll have a month off to apply to colleges before I do a semester at FLC, the local college.

Before that, I have 300 pages of 10 point font of a book to read before tomorrow, so I should probably get off.  Love ya all, and hope to hear from you.

SO if people haven't noticed, I am taking a break from LJ.  I have more stuff than god intended to get done before school starts, and I'm sorta paying attention to myspace and hi5 or whatever it is.  I just can't find Valeria and it's making me sad.

Actually, I'm posting less and less to this journal, and more to my private one.  This is partly a result of things in my life getting complicated and private, and partly because I'm actually becoming self-reliant.  Anyway, hope everyone is grand, and talk to ya later.  If it's impotante, email at brindalin@gmail.com

So I never exactly got to tell about the last weekend. I don't have much time tonight, but I'll try and fill some people in. I went with the Excel Steel Band (My old school's band, has around 10 steel pans, guitars, bass, drums, keyboards, kinda big this summer) to first Creed, a small Colorado town, and then the Crestone music festival. Creed was a small gig, but fun, and warmed us up for Crestone. We drove to Crestone and camped there Saturday night. Then Sunday morning we played, and llistened to the other bands until we had to go.
I will say this; in short, Crestone was a blast. There were some incredible bands there, big names and great music. The dancing alone was worth it, I got to dance to salsa, latin, blues, classic jazz, and other random genre's, all new to me. (In that I haven't danced to them before) I got to dance with Ale, Nicolei and Kista, who are all fun girls. (Krista in particular had a very similar style to me, and I loved dancing with her.   I got to dance in the rain, which was totally new, and entirely awesome.  Booyah!
The music itself was a lot of fun also.  We were obviously the lower end in the spectrum as far as quality, I think we were there because of a "affirmative action" program getting young bands there.  I don't care, it was just awesome.  The people there were just amazingly nice, mostly hippies, but all types.  I got a fucking free massage from a guy there; it is easily the best one I have ever had.  A lot of the more stoner types stayed up late and played african style drums into the night 'round a bonfire.  I really enjoyed hanging out with them a bit, talking to entirely random people about the most random things.   (If this is what I get for staying up late, I'll be doing it a lot more often.
So the trip was awesome except for one issue that I'm not really going to say.   Partly my fault, party not my fault, all bad feelings.  Blerg, it depresses me.

Emhem.  On to other things.

Soooo, I almost died today.  It was pretty bizarre.  Blake was working with the garlic, and I the maters (tomatoes).  I asked Blake to pass me a bowl which was sitting next to him.  He threw it Frisbee style, like we always do in a busy kitchen.  I look to catch it and held out my hands.

About then, I notice something coming up from the bowl.  This may sound like BS, (I wouldn't believe myself),  but time seriously got all slow-mow.  I remember seeing this knife slide out of the bowl with that *shink* sound, and starting spinning towards me.    It's bizarre, since I've almost killed myself many, many times in different ways, and never had any other reaction than the predictable rush of adrenalin.  This time... it was fricken creepy, even for me.  reality just shouldn't work that way.  I swear it took five minutes in my little "matrix zone" for the knife to spin right up to me, and it wasn't until the last millisecond that I realized it was going to hit me with the handle.  That left most of five minutes of distorted reality to question if I was going to get a knife stuck in my throat.

Obviously, it did not, though I have a little bruise that stings occasionally.  It shouldn't last another day, but I'm still in a strange sort of shock.  Why did this happen?   Why the hell did I decide to get all "Life flashy before the eyes?"  (Thought it really didn't, I just remember having around twenty different thoughts of things I'd done in the past couple weeks, things that I regretted, things that i treasured.  Little stuff, stupid stuff to be honest.  I regret not being clear to people about my humanity; I often portray the image that I am lot better of a person than I actually am.  Not that I can't be that person, I just am not him most of the time.  I fuck up things, I make really bad mistakes, and I'm not always as truthful as I could be.  I can't even have a decent flash back before I die for Christ's sake.  
SO it's over now and I wonder what the hell happened, why it happened, and what I'm going to do now. 

I have no fucking idea.

And there goes two years of my life.  What the Fuck?  I guess we are really that shallow, this sucks!  If moving means feeling sad because I'll miss important people, than I want to actually miss them, not just sorta morn for a week then feel like I haven't seen them for a couple of years.  Bloody hell.'

As of yet, I haven't figured out what the hell to do about it.  I learning long ago that my feelings will do whatever the fuck they want and bummer if I don't like them.  This leaves a lot of drugs, intense therapy or..  I don't know.   The whole situation is fucked, this is the first time in a whole fricken while that I'm upset because I can't feel bad emotions.  A whole bleeding long time.

Grrr, I am angst embodied.  This fact does not, however, make the situation less suckier.

So if anyone has ideas on how to feel more sad about feeling things, feel free to share.  (Dear god I can't believe I said that)


Oh, and Dana, who left the knife in the bowl, (big no-no at carvers) got a warning, and is suspended for a week.  I'm just wierded out by the whole situation.

Ned, for some reason which is unknown to me, was happy to see me, and thanked me for bidding ado. Soo anyway, somehow he got me happy, upon which I returned to vlockbuster and bought much less depressing movies.  My decision now fits who I am, instead of how ppathetic I am. So I've started at Carvers, and am currently working a M-W-F schedule which lets me go to band on tuesdays and thursdays. Sweetness embodied. People rely much less on my instintanious actions, and falling behind is less of a problem. Also; I make more money, can socialize more, get less wet and dirty, and am all in all more relaxed. Win-win: I win, and I win again. I've only worked two days now, and am already getting bored of getting wasted after work. Strange huh? That was all I could think of during school, drowning myself in Alcohol, but it gets very boring very quickly. Or not boring, but... plain. My taste for beer has increased though, I really enjoy the light rasberry ale and brokeback beers they have. (Yes, that is in fact named after the movie.) Now it's far too late to really do anything about it but get ready to suffer next year, but for what it's worth I know the truth now. Damn it all. I can't believe Janet ended up fucking me over in this manner. Talk of bizarrity. But I blame others. I should have used my head a little more, and actually trusted my own damn feelings instead others's fears. Learn something new every day! Band, Carvers, Dnd, Videogames, Real friends, Hot chicks who are also my friends (Dalin is not allowed to read that line) Alcohol, Colorado, Camping, Durango, Teh animus,God, I just love flipping everything here. Except my parents, but I can deal with them remarkable easily for a change. I even like this house for a change. Hmm, probably other stuff too, but I'm tired and am going to try and pretend I can get to sleep. Love you, and goodnight everyone. And remember, brush your teeth kids!

I hope I can save myself from failure, but it may be unavoidable. Once school is over though, I'm going to be on cloud 9. Thinking of this summer is outright intoxicating, and I get way too caught up to do anything else. I zoned through my entire morning today thinking of stoner (buckly) park of all places. My relationship to Durango is that classic situation where I didn't care until I left-- now it means everything to me. Funny, that. I just hope I can make it to then. Also check out Goblins, a DnD comic which is most deffinetly not your standard DnD comic. So for the next month these are my goals: a) Survive School B) get the hell out of this state C) See Dalin more D) Get the hell out of this state E) Get to Durango F) Get really wasted, and forget every single thing about this year (except Dalin) G) Party Hard with Alex and friends H) Get the hell out of this state *To heavy guitar riff* "Here I go again on my own going down the only road I've ever known like a drifter i was born to walk alone I've made up my mind I ain't wasting no more time (Repeat)" Peace out everyone, love ya all.

So obviously I did not manage to update on monday night, which should have been suspected. I got home and was immediately sucked into Morrowind, a new RPG I bought. Why am I not doing the same now? Mostly because I'm at someone else's house whose computer lacks Morrowind, but that is an insignificant detail! Ignoring my usual pontification, I have just completed my fourth day of college searching. I have yet to be unhappy with a school as of yet, which I guess is good and bad. This means I will still have to make a difficult decision come next April, (Assuming I'm accepted to a few of these colleges) but I do know that if I don't make it into any particular college I'll be perfectly happy somewhere else. In the end, I'll do fine wherever I go. If anyone wants a particularly detailed description on any of the forementioned colleges, I'll be happy to supply one, but boiled down they're like this: Bard; exotic liberal free-for-all. Drew: Prestigious middler. Gettysburg; my-parents-went-here college. Trinity; kegger, I'm-smart-and-thus-can-party-better-than-you college. Mind you, they all lie under the liberal art colleges, so these are vague tendencies under that category. And I still have Connecticut College to go. Might even hit Westlyian on the way home. In any case, I could be happy at any one. It will just depend on my mood at the time of final decision. Or perhaps I'll just roll a d20. Classy, don'tjahthink? Beyond just the damn colleges, it's been a pretty nice week. Wenesday night we got home, but tuesday was spen in a cheap motal in Gettyseburg. I didn't mind the crappy room; the hotel was literaly next to the huge gettysburg graveyard which essentially holds every dead guy and gal who died in that town in the previous 200 years. I've always found the dead peaceful; a happy change from their more lively counterparts. I spent most of Tuesday afternoon just strolling past the gravestones and lying on the grass. I will never understand why no one visits graveyards. Even leaving out the guilt factor of visiting loved ones past, they are peaceful and wonderful places. I can never feel lonely in a graveyard, it seems that I'm just a spectator of all the remaining peaces of past generations. I'm articulating this horribly, but the final message should be something like this. Renny like graveyards. Renny spend many hours in large peaceful and empty graveyard. Renny Happy. The only difficult part about either tuesday or wenesday was that both involved a great deal of driving. 5 and a half hour to be exact. But I survived, mostly through extensive use of the ipod, and thus lived to drive another day.
Blerg, I'm getting tired. I'll wrap up with a quick description of this afternoon. We left Trinity come 3 or so, and arived at Robin's house in an hour. Robin is my mother's friend in someway that I don't know, and wouldn't care, except for the fact that she's rich. She has a huge house on a beautiful lake somewhere out of Hartford, and it's to kill for. I got here, hot, tired, grumpy and hosting a headache that would down an adult rinocerous. somehow my mother got the hint, and I was left along in my new romm to cool down. I read a little, then came down to the lake. Robin was kind enough o offer a kyack she had, which I took off with. It proved to be just the thing I needed. The lake is beautiful, I mean really just perfect. It's the kind of lake that people come from foreign countries to see, and I was the only one on it. I just sorta paddled up and down, into this nook, out of that, i alternated just lying in the fading light on the soft water, letting it rock my troubles away. One thing my father has managed to instill in me for all my resistance is a deep love of nature in it's purer forms. well this was just what I needed; I went up and down the lake. near the top, I found a small inlet in what seems a host of huge water reeds, and I followed it for a surrising distance up the lake. As a crow flies it waasn't all that long, but the only channel through all the cottentails winded up and down, turning it into a long trip. Aparently it's some ind of bird habitat, for I could not look a single direction befor seeing some new bird. There was this pair of swans which seemed very curious in my affairs and followed me from a distance until they got bord and went fishing. I also spotted a few ospreys diving into the lake, just beautiful really. I was tired wet and cold when I came back, but truely refreshed. I came in to a wonderful roaring fire that was set up. Yeah, just wow. A glass of wine, a comfortabe pillow, and I reached nirvana a couple of days before the bloody dali-lama. Even a dull lecture on how my college choices were irresponsible by Robin's husband couldn't lower my spirits, for I have had one God Blessed afternoon!!!
...And now I'm really bloody tired. I love you all, hope everyone's life is in the end as peaceful as my day to days was. Sorry if this piece is grammatical retching, I've no time to check it over or even read it once for that matter. I've just enough time to wish everyone a wonderful night, and fall into bed. "All that is gold does not glitter, not all those who wander are lost; the old that is strong does not wither, deep roots are not reached by the frost. "

<lj-cut text="Spring Break Episode I: Extreme Pontification">So... yeah, I'm really lame.  Instead of going on some nihilistic rant like my last post, I will do a little to explain myself and try and make it up, and we shall see if it works.

First of all, no, I'm not dead, I haven't been abducted by aliens, or kidnapped by a ferocious tribe of Amazonian lesbians for forced procreation, (no?  damn!) I'm still here in the pit of Bethel, Hell, Connecticut.  I am about three-quarters through my Junior year, which is proving about as enjoyable as middle school.  (Which is to say, not at all)  I have missed ungodly amounts of school this year thanks to a series of resons.  (read: excuses)  
First of all, my immune system has apparently decieced to take a vacation, leaving me open to every bug on the bacterial (or viral) market.  I've been out with flu, bronchitis, (spwelled wright!) multi-cold, fever, stomach problems, normal headaches, and sever migraines.  Granted, a considerable amount of this is due to my terrible constitution and not just the various diseases present here.  I do however suspect that I'm not used to the many strains of illness that propagate the rabbles of New England.  
I have also just been having issues with life.  My medication Lexipro, which treats my depression has proved very succesful, but results in a few side-effects.  My moods are more stable, to be sure, but I am much more prone to anger and general I'm-pissed-off-at-the-world syndrome, which I really didn't experiencce before.  Mind you, I'd rather deal with this than manic-depression anyday, but it does result in a few days missed from school for "personal reasons".  I also have a few minor sexual side-effects, but let's not get into that...
AHEM.  So with missing a lot of school, one would guess that my grades have been suffering.  They have, but I have hopefully managed to keep at least lower A's for this last quater, although that may not be the case.  Only time will tell.
Which brings us to my future in scholarship.  As per usual Junior actions, I am looking in to colleges to go to, and visiting them during spring break.  Which in this next week FYI.  My current attributes I am intersted in are some of the following; small to medium size, decent atmosphere and campus life, laid back rules, pretty good tech facilities and computer science department, poly sci stuff, nice doorms for most undergrads, and hots chicks.  Wait, did I say hot chicks?  I mean bitches.
Which ever colleges proceeds to score the highest from that list will be then ranked by how much they're will to pay for my tuition.  Then I shall attend for a few years and learn a few things, get wasted a whole lot, hopefully lose something starting with a V, possibly find out what I want to do with my life, and just have fun. Speaking Of things that start will V, everyone should go see V for Vendetta but I'm going on tangent.
During this spring break, (17th to the 21st) I will be visiting five colleges in the following order; Bard college in Clinton, NY, Dre University in Madison NJ, Gettysburg college in PA, and Trinity and Connecticut COllege in CT.    Twill be a full, busy week, but I hope to get a good comparitive grasp of Liberals Arts colleges in Northeast, if nothing else.  Hints, suggestions, ideas, compliments and insults are all welcome in this large and complicated search.  Especially from those who have gone through college and what they think of it afterwards.

BLerg, away from responsible stuff, I feel I should offer the following disclaimer that I gave Ale, as it rings as true as ever:
"Renny is no more. The entity previously known as Renny has been consumed by a variety of sub-conscious parasites, and all that remains is a husk of a body and a few memories on the internet. He has betrayed his friends, forgotten his family, and left his interests to the dust. Perhaps is some civilization centuries from now, someone will come across the fragments that make up Renny's conscious, and bring him back to life. Until then, you will just have to read his really lame ass live journal and try and believe the lame ass excuses that a known imposter puts in his place for not attending to any part of life. If you see this imposter, do your best to kill him/her or in some way incapacitate him/her so that he/she will have no more sick and twisted power over Renny's previous friends. Acid works well, as does gunshots to the head. Best of luck, and may Renny's glowy, Obi-Wan-like ghost be with you."
So yeah, I guess everyone should be making death threats on me, should make things interesting at least.

Lesse, I've really got to go now, but I'll try and continue this manana if Bard doesn't kill me.  I will also try and actually check up on the friends I have deserted, whether they be in CO or CT.  
For a final exit,

                    "Remember, remember, the fifth of
                    November, the gunpowder treason and
                    plot.  I know of now reason why the
                    gunpowder treason should ever be
                    forgot."

A quick update to assure people that I am not, in fact, as dead as they think. I may have decomposed to corpse-like-appearence, but my lungs still pull in air, and I still play Counter-Strike like a maniac. I apologize for neglecting livjournal, life has decieded that I should do other things. Or, I guess I have, inadvertanly, but doing those other things. Either way, I shall try and make a bigger update tomorrow when I have the energy. Firstly an anime report. I have purchased the entire Cowboy Bebop series, and watched it all just as quickly. And dear god it is wonderful. I cried my heart out on several occasions, but I love Bebop more now than I love oxygen. More recently I have been watching Gumdam Seed as lent to me by Dalin and Brian. While not Cowboy Bebop, Gundam Seed is still engagin enough to make me forget everything else when I have a new disc. (I've been lent the episodes in pairs; curse it all) And lasty, while not actually anime, I've been watching Xombie; a short flash series on the internet and enjoying it. Go look it up, its short, has zombies, and has zombies. Fun for the whole family. Other news says I am barely surviving my Junior year of high school, and my A average looks very precarious from here. Wish me luck everyone, cause I'm gonna damn well need it. School is mostly what holds me from updating this thing more often. Also: I have the best girlfriend ever, and I'm sure God will get pissed that I've been so lucky and smite me soon. Maybe. Blerg, that was mostly usless drivel. Except for the last thing, but I don't feel like explaining that right now. Lastly I have obtained all Rammstein Albums known to man (Maybe women now about some I don't) and have heard enough to put them as my thrid favorite band ahead of the Beatles. Let the skies fall and the mountains crumble. That comment was totally inapropriate. IF anyone wants to hear a truely awesome, divine, kickass song, look up Stirb Nicht Vor Mir (Don't Die Before I Do) from the album Rosenrot. It's a beautiful duet sung in German by the rammstein lead, and in english by a talented young woman. I may be an over-sensitive-melodramatic-fool, but this song makes me want to cry, and be really happy at the same time-- a neat combination. Renout.

Fae was just starting to understand her place in the universe, and Spike goes and gets himself killed while killing Viscious.  It's not fair!

GAH!!!  I am pathtic.  A sorry excuse for a man.  I can't even pull myself together to get some damned chores done, and I put them off till I finished the DVDs.

..noooo!!!!!
